===COMMANDS===
fisrt install WSL2 in windows (using POWERSHELL)

run POWERSHELL as administrator
Enable-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online -FeatureName Microsoft-Windows-Subsystem-Linux (TYPE THIS CODE IN POWERSHELL)

RESTART computer 

dism.exe /online /enable-feature /featurename:VirtualMachinePlatform /all /norestart (TYPE THIS CODE IN POWERSHELL)
dism.exe /online /enable-feature /featurename:Microsoft-Windows-Subsystem-Linux /all /norestart (TYPE THIS CODE IN POWERSHELL)

RESTART computer

AND
INSTALL LINUX KERNEL IN WINDOWS 
https://aka.ms/wsl2kernel (USE THIS LINK)

SET DEFAULT TO WSL 2
wsl --set-default-version 2 (TYPE THIS CODE IN POWERSHELL)

CHECK VERSION AND LINUX RUNING OR NOT
wsl --list --verbose (TYPE THIS CODE IN POWERSHELL)

AND
INSTALL KALI LINUX IN WINDOWS

OPEN WINDOWS STORE AND TYPE KALI IN SEARCH BOX INSTALL KALI LINUX
SET USERNAME AND PASSWORD
UPDATE AND UPGRADE THE KALI LINUX
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y (TYPE THIS CODE IN KALI LINUX)
sudo apt install kali-desktop-xfce -y (TYPE THIS CODE IN KALI LINUX)

INSTALL XRDP
sudo apt install xrdp -y (TYPE THIS CODE IN KALI LINUX)

AND START THE XRDP SERVICE
sudo service xrdp start (TYPE THIS CODE IN KALI LINUX)

IF YOUR FACE ANY ERROR PULL REQEST TO ME 


